          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">A</hi> BARD, on whom Phœbus his spirit bestow'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-2" n="2">Resolving t' acknowledge the bounty he ow'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-3" n="3">Found out a new method at once of confessing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-4" n="4">And making the most of so mighty a blessing:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-5" n="5">To the God he·'d be grateful; but mortals he·'d chouse,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-6" n="6">By making his patron preside in his house;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-7" n="7">And wisely foresaw this advantage from thence,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-8" n="8">That the God would in honour bear most of th' expence:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-9" n="9">So the bard he finds drink, and leaves Phœbus to treat</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-10" n="10">With the thoughts he inspires, regardless of meat.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-11" n="11">Hence they, that come hither expecting to dine,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-262-79L1-line-12" n="12">Are always fobb'd off with sheer wit and sheer wine.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
